HEADWORD: Toman
<hw>To*man"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>t⟦omac⟧m⟦amac⟧n</ets>; from a Mongol word signifying, ten
thousand.]</ety> <def>A money of account in Persia, whose value varies
greatly at different times and places. Its average value may be reckoned
at about two and a half dollars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

